<section id="mobile-push-android-creds" role="topic">
    <sectioninfo>
        <abstract>
            <para>Describes how to get push messaging credentials for a Firebase or Google Cloud
                Platform project.</para>
        </abstract>
    </sectioninfo>
    <title id="mobile-push-android-creds.title">Step 2: Get Push Messaging Credentials for
        Android</title>
    <para>To send push notifications to Android apps, you must have credentials from either
        &FCMlong; (&FCM;) or its predecessor, &GCMlong; (&GCM;). The credentials are a server key
        and a sender ID (also called project number). You get these credentials from a project that
        has push messaging enabled. This project could either be in the Firebase console or the
        Google Cloud Platform console, depending on where you created it.</para>
    <para>This topic describes how to retrieve your credentials from FCM or GCM. Use FCM for new
        Android apps. Use GCM only if you have a preexisting GCM project that you have not yet
        updated for FCM support.</para>
    <procedure>
        <title>To obtain your credentials from FCM</title>
        <step>
            <para>Go to the Firebase console at <ulink url="https://console.firebase.google.com/"
                    >https://console.firebase.google.com/</ulink> and open your project.</para>
        </step>
        <step>
            <para>In the left pane, to the right of your project name, choose the gear icon, and
                then choose <guilabel>Project Settings</guilabel>.</para>
            <?oxy_insert_start author="jacowarr" timestamp="20170202T173816-0800"?>
            <mediaobject>
                <imageobject>
                    <imagedata
                        fileref="&url-doc-domain;images/en_us/mobile-shared/mobile-push/push-fcm-project-settings.png"
                        format="PNG" width="100%" scalefit="1" contentdepth="100%"/>
                </imageobject>
                <textobject>
                    <phrase><?oxy_insert_end?>Project Settings
                        option.<?oxy_insert_start author="jacowarr" timestamp="20170202T173816-0800"?></phrase>
                </textobject>
            </mediaobject>
            <?oxy_insert_end?>
        </step>
        <step>
            <para>In the top menu, choose <guilabel>Cloud Messaging</guilabel>.</para>
            <?oxy_insert_start author="jacowarr" timestamp="20170202T173816-0800"?>
            <mediaobject>
                <imageobject>
                    <imagedata
                        fileref="&url-doc-domain;images/en_us/mobile-shared/mobile-push/push-fcm-project-messaging.png"
                        format="PNG" width="100%" scalefit="1" contentdepth="100%"/>
                </imageobject>
                <textobject>
                    <phrase><?oxy_insert_end?>Cloud Messaging
                        tab.<?oxy_insert_start author="jacowarr" timestamp="20170202T173816-0800"?></phrase>
                </textobject>
            </mediaobject>
            <?oxy_insert_end?>
        </step>
        <step>
            <para>Under <guilabel>Project credentials</guilabel>, you will find the server key and
                sender ID. Save these values somewhere you can access later.</para>
        </step>
    </procedure>
    <procedure>
        <title>To obtain your credentials from GCM</title>
        <step>
            <para>Go to the Google API Console at <ulink url="https://console.developers.google.com"
                    >https://console.developers.google.com</ulink>.</para>
        </step>
        <step>
            <para>In the left pane, choose <guilabel>Credentials</guilabel>.</para>
            <?oxy_insert_start author="jacowarr" timestamp="20170202T173816-0800"?>
            <mediaobject>
                <imageobject>
                    <imagedata
                        fileref="&url-doc-domain;images/en_us/mobile-shared/mobile-push/push-gcm-credentials-in-menu.png"
                        format="PNG" width="100%" scalefit="1" contentdepth="100%"/>
                </imageobject>
                <textobject>
                    <phrase><?oxy_insert_end?>Credentials.<?oxy_insert_start author="jacowarr" timestamp="20170202T173816-0800"?></phrase>
                </textobject>
            </mediaobject>
            <?oxy_insert_end?>
        </step>
        <step>
            <para>If you already have credentials for your app, your server key is shown in the
                    <guilabel>API keys</guilabel> section. Save this key somewhere you can access
                later.</para>
        </step>
        <step>
            <para>If you don't have credentials for your app, the console displays the
                    <guilabel>Credentials</guilabel> dialog box. Create a server key by completing
                the following steps:</para>
            <substeps>
                <step>
                    <para>Choose <guilabel>Create credentials</guilabel>.</para>
                    <?oxy_insert_start author="jacowarr" timestamp="20170202T173816-0800"?>
                    <mediaobject>
                        <imageobject>
                            <imagedata
                                fileref="&url-doc-domain;images/en_us/mobile-shared/mobile-push/push-gcm-credentials-create.png"
                                format="PNG" width="100%" scalefit="1" contentdepth="100%"/>
                        </imageobject>
                        <textobject>
                            <phrase><?oxy_insert_end?>Create credentials
                                button.<?oxy_insert_start author="jacowarr" timestamp="20170202T173816-0800"?></phrase>
                        </textobject>
                    </mediaobject>
                    <?oxy_insert_end?>
                </step>
                <step>
                    <para>Save the API key somewhere you can access later.</para>
                    <?oxy_insert_start author="jacowarr" timestamp="20170202T173816-0800"?>
                    <mediaobject>
                        <imageobject>
                            <imagedata
                                fileref="&url-doc-domain;images/en_us/mobile-shared/mobile-push/push-gcm-credentials-api-key-display.png"
                                format="PNG" width="100%" scalefit="1" contentdepth="100%"/>
                        </imageobject>
                        <textobject>
                            <phrase><?oxy_insert_end?>API
                                key.<?oxy_insert_start author="jacowarr" timestamp="20170202T173816-0800"?></phrase>
                        </textobject>
                    </mediaobject>
                    <?oxy_insert_end?>
                </step>
            </substeps>
        </step>
        <step>
            <para>To retrieve your sender ID (also called project number), go to the Google Cloud
                Platform console at <ulink url="https://console.cloud.google.com/"/>. Select your
                project from the <guilabel>Project</guilabel> menu. Then, choose the down arrow next
                to the project name.</para>
            <?oxy_insert_start author="jacowarr" timestamp="20170202T173816-0800"?>
            <mediaobject>
                <imageobject>
                    <imagedata
                        fileref="&url-doc-domain;images/en_us/mobile-shared/mobile-push/push-gcm-credentials-expand-project.png"
                        format="PNG" width="100%" scalefit="1" contentdepth="100%"/>
                </imageobject>
                <textobject>
                    <phrase><?oxy_insert_end?>A project in the Google Cloud Platform
                        console.<?oxy_insert_start author="jacowarr" timestamp="20170202T173816-0800"?></phrase>
                </textobject>
            </mediaobject>
            <?oxy_insert_end?>
        </step>
        <step>
            <para>Save the displayed project number somewhere you can access later.</para>
            <note>
                <para>Project number is another name for sender ID.</para>
            </note>
            <?oxy_insert_start author="jacowarr" timestamp="20170202T173816-0800"?>
            <mediaobject>
                <imageobject>
                    <imagedata
                        fileref="&url-doc-domain;images/en_us/mobile-shared/mobile-push/push-gcm-credentials-expand-project.png"
                        format="PNG" width="100%" scalefit="1" contentdepth="100%"/>
                </imageobject>
                <textobject>
                    <phrase><?oxy_insert_end?>The project number in the Google Cloud Platform
                        console.<?oxy_insert_start author="jacowarr" timestamp="20170202T173816-0800"?></phrase>
                </textobject>
            </mediaobject>
            <?oxy_insert_end?>
        </step>
    </procedure>
